climbs.name: S. O. S.
climbs.fa: Marty Karabin and Harvey de los Rios (4/91)

content.description: Like the other routes here- this starts in a bulge and then flows into a vertical face. This route definitely needs another bolt (EBR)and loses a star in quality and enjoyment.
content.location: This is the 2nd sport route from the right. Just left of a 2 bolt face (Treading Water 5.10c).

climbs.name: Fish Food
climbs.fa: Harvey de los Rios and Marty Karabin (4/91)

content.description: A tiny route that starts on a steep section before getting less steep. Origionaly rated 10a though we thought it to be definitely sand bagged, or at least, severely eroded by rush hour traffic.
content.protection: Two (2) bolts. While its been written that a small  camming unit will go in before the 1st bolt- we thought this to be not very responsible by the first ascentionists and would recommend stick-clipping.
content.location: Lies near the center of the wall to the right of a highball boulder problem that follows a right-tending crack.

climbs.name: Coal Fire
climbs.fa: Marty Karabin and Harvey de los Rios (4/91)

content.description: Crux is low down on the route- definitely easier if taller. Climbs over bulge onto standard face.
content.location: Just to the right of Fish Food in the center of the wall.

content.description: This short north-facing cliff sits atop a hill straight south from the Hook Wall across the wash.
